---
import KilocodeLayout from "../../layouts/KilocodeLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/cheatsheet-shared.css";
---

<KilocodeLayout
  title="Kilo Code Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes | changelogs.info"
  description="Get Kilo Code installed and running in 10 minutes. VS Code extension for AI-assisted coding with MCP tool support."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="cs-wrapper">

    <section class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__emoji">🤖</div>
      <h1 class="kc-headline cs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="cs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="cs-hero__sub">Up and running in 10 minutes — VS Code extension for AI-assisted coding with MCP tool support and task history.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="cs-grid">

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="kc-headline cs-panel__title">Prerequisites</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">VS Code 1.85+</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Required editor. Check with <code>code --version</code></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="kc-headline cs-panel__title">Install</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Install from VS Code Marketplace</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Open VS Code → Extensions (Cmd+Shift+X) → search "Kilo Code" → Install</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="kc-headline cs-panel__title">First Run</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">1. Open the command palette</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Press <code>Cmd+Shift+P</code> (macOS) or <code>Ctrl+Shift+P</code> (Windows/Linux)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">2. Start a new task</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Type "Kilo Code: New Task" and describe what you want to do.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="kc-headline cs-panel__title">First Real Task</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Explain selected code</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Select a function in your editor, then <code>Cmd+Shift+P</code> → "Kilo Code: Explain Selection". Kilo Code breaks down the logic and explains each part.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="kc-headline cs-panel__title">What Next?</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Set up MCP tools</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Configure MCP tools for your stack to multiply what Kilo Code can do — database queries, API calls, deployment.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Enable auto-approve for routine edits</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Speed up your workflow by auto-approving low-risk operations like formatting and simple refactors.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/kilocode/cheatsheet/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Cheatsheet →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">All the commands and workflows at a glance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/kilocode/tips/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Tips & Tricks →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Quick wins, hidden features, and common mistakes to avoid.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/kilocode/changelog/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Changelog →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Stay up to date with every release.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/kilocode/configs/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Configs →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Configuration reference and recommended settings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</KilocodeLayout>
